# PM Module Role Hierarchy Restructuring

## Problem Statement

The current PM module is **flat** — anyone with the `pm` module assigned can see **all** projects, create projects, assign anyone, and manage everything. There is no concept of:

- **PM Lead** (head of the PM department — assigns projects to individual Project Managers)
- **Project Manager** (owns specific projects — assigns Team Leads and Team Members within their projects)
- **Team Lead** / **Team Member** (work on assigned tasks within their projects)

Additionally, the **Admin dashboard** currently shows PM stats inline (active projects, pending tasks, milestones) as static badges — there's no clickable "PM Overview" page where Admin can drill into all projects.

---

## Refined Requirements (What You're Asking For)

Based on my analysis of your codebase and your request, here is what I understand you want:

### 1. Role Hierarchy within PM Module

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["Admin (God view — sees everything)"] --> B["PM Lead (1 person — assigns projects to PMs)"]
    B --> C1["Project Manager 1"]
    B --> C2["Project Manager 2"]
    B --> C3["Project Manager N"]
    C1 --> D1["Team Lead A"]
    C1 --> D2["Team Member B"]
    C1 --> D3["Team Member C"]
    C2 --> D4["Team Lead D"]
    C2 --> D5["Team Member E"]
```

- **Admin**: Read-only oversight of all PM data. Does NOT create projects. Gets a dedicated "PM Overview" page (not inline stats on the dashboard).
- **PM Lead**: Creates projects and assigns them to individual **Project Managers**. Can see all projects aggregated.
- **Project Manager**: Owns their assigned projects. Can assign **Team Leads** and **Team Members**. Sees only their own projects on their dashboard.
- **Team Lead / Team Member**: Sees only the projects they are part of. Team Lead may have limited management abilities (e.g., update task status, assign sub-tasks).

### 2. Individual Project Manager Dashboard

Each Project Manager should see:
- Only **their own projects** (not all projects in the system)
- Cumulative task distribution across their projects (e.g., X pending, Y in-progress, Z done)
- Team workload view — how many tasks are assigned to each team member across their projects

### 3. Admin PM Overview (Refactored)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Your current admin dashboard** has a "PM Overview" card (lines 126–156 in `admin/dashboard.html`) showing static badges for active projects, completed projects, pending tasks, and milestones. You want to:
> 1. **Remove** this inline PM Overview from the admin dashboard
> 2. **Replace it with a link** to a dedicated `/admin/pm-overview` page
> 3. That page shows **all projects** with progress, task distribution, team allocation — a full read-only overview

