## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### Q1: Should Admin be above PM Lead?
> **Currently:** Admin has `is_admin=True` and bypasses all module checks. They can already access the PM module and see everything.
>
> **My recommendation:** Yes, Admin should remain **above** PM Lead. Admin has god-mode access to everything but does NOT actively manage projects (read-only oversight). PM Lead is the operational head of project management. This keeps separation of concerns clean.
>
> **Do you agree**, or do you want Admin to also be able to create/assign projects?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### Q2: How do we designate someone as "PM Lead" vs "Project Manager"?
> Currently, all PM module users are equal. We need a way to distinguish roles. Options:
>
> **Option A:** Add a `pm_role` field to the `User` model: `pm_lead`, `project_manager`, `team_lead`, `team_member`
>
> **Option B:** Use the existing `ProjectMember.role` field — PM Lead is anyone who creates a project and assigns a PM; Project Managers are added to projects with role = "Project Manager"
>
> **Option C:** Create a separate `pm_role` column on the `user_modules` table so roles are module-specific
>
> **Which approach do you prefer?** I recommend **Option A** for simplicity.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### Q3: Can there be multiple PM Leads, or strictly one?
> You said "have a PM Lead" (singular). Should there be:
> - **Exactly one** PM Lead in the system (like a CTO for projects)?
> - **Multiple** PM Leads (e.g., one per department)?

> [!WARNING]
> ### Q4: Should Project Managers only see their own projects?
> Right now, the PM dashboard shows ALL projects. If we scope it per-PM, then:
> - PM Lead sees **all projects** (aggregate view)
> - Project Manager sees **only projects assigned to them**
> - Team members see **only projects they're part of**
>
> **Is this the scoping you want?**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### Q5: What does "assign a project to a Project Manager" mean?
> Currently, `Project.created_by` stores who created the project, and `ProjectMember` stores team members with roles. Should we:
>
> **Option A:** Add a new field `Project.assigned_pm` (FK to `users.id`) — the PM responsible for the project
>
> **Option B:** Use `ProjectMember` with `role = 'Project Manager'` — the PM is just a special member
>
> **I recommend Option A** — a project has exactly one assigned PM, plus team members.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### Q6: What should the PM Lead's dashboard show?
> Options:
> - **All projects** grouped by Project Manager (who owns what)
> - **Cumulative stats** across all PMs (total tasks, bottlenecks, delayed projects)
> - **PM performance metrics** (how many tasks are each PM's team completing)
>
> **What level of detail do you want?**

> [!NOTE]
> ### Q7: Team Lead vs Team Member permissions
> Should Team Leads have any extra permissions compared to Team Members? For example:
> - Can Team Leads assign tasks to team members?
> - Can Team Leads update task status for others?
> - Or are they just a label?

> [!NOTE]
> ### Q8: What about existing data?
> The seed data has `pm_lead` (Rahul Verma) as a user with `pm` module access. After this change:
> - Should `pm_lead` become the PM Lead role?
> - Should `john_doe` (who has `pm` module) become a Project Manager or Team Member?
> - Do we need to update seed data to reflect the new hierarchy?

